We talked about press freedom on Labor Day. World Press Freedom Day, May 3, is in less than 36 hours. Let's not forget the two are closely related. Journalism is also a profession. Media practitioners aren't paid well and work long hours. Add to that libel cases filed just to harass, unjust contractualization schemes, death threats both online and offline, and actual media killings, and you get a pretty ugly picture of what being a journalist means. BREAKING: President Duterte expands Sotto Law to include broadcast, digital media. With the signing of Republic Act (RA) No. 11458, online and broadcast journalists may now be allowed to refuse to reveal their sources. Republic Act (RA) No. 11458 amends RA No. 53 or the Sotto law which previously only covered print media like newspapers and magazines.…
